ture. We find that the subradiant\nstates fall into two categories at finite temperature: one that is temperature\nindependent and one that acquires temperature dependence. With the RWA there is\nno temperature dependence in any case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Dec 2010 18:34:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Jan 2011 00:03:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 26 May 2011 16:42:48 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2011 05:34:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-17"}
